<subSubSection id="C32D63FDDE4EFFF1FF3FF0C2FBC54FD1" lastPageId="17" lastPageNumber="33" pageId="16" pageNumber="32" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B883076DE4EFFF0FF3FF0C2FEDD4EEA" blockId="16.[189,335,669,695]" box="[189,335,669,695]" pageId="16" pageNumber="32">
<heading id="D0C0871ADE4EFFF0FF3FF0C2FEDD4EEA" bold="true" box="[189,335,669,695]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="16" pageNumber="32" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B943EC64DE4EFFF0FF3FF0C2FEDD4EEA" bold="true" box="[189,335,669,695]" pageId="16" pageNumber="32">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B883076DE4EFFF1FF3FF093FBC54FD1" blockId="16.[189,1398,716,742]" lastBlockId="17.[188,1399,670,908]" lastPageId="17" lastPageNumber="33" pageId="16" pageNumber="32">
Colony unilaminar, encrusting. Autozooids hexagonal, rounded distally (
<figureCitation id="130C2CF3DE4EFFF0FBB2F093FB334EBB" box="[1072,1185,716,742]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="17.[189,232,1894,1920]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,1037,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-192@17.[189,1398,1037,1853]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Fig. 11. Labioporella hariparensis Guha &amp; Gopikrishna, 2007 (GIS/B 0533). A. General view of the colony showing autozooids. B. Enlargement of an autozooid showing cryptocyst and polypide tube. C. Close-up of the colony showing autozooid with proximal tubercles. D. Enlargement of the colony showing ancestrula and interzooecial avicularia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6580806" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6580806/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="32">Fig. 11A</figureCitation>
). Lateral margins beaded, thickly calcified, raised in relation to autozooidal frontal shield; autozooidal boundaries also marked by thin grooves. Cryptocyst coarsely granular, occupying nearly ⅔ of autozooidal frontal surface and descending smoothly into the orifice; polypide tube slender, opening into the orifice with mediumsized lateral indentations (
<figureCitation id="130C2CF3DE4FFFF1FE6FF157FDC44F7F" box="[493,598,776,802]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="17.[189,232,1894,1920]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,1037,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-192@17.[189,1398,1037,1853]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Fig. 11. Labioporella hariparensis Guha &amp; Gopikrishna, 2007 (GIS/B 0533). A. General view of the colony showing autozooids. B. Enlargement of an autozooid showing cryptocyst and polypide tube. C. Close-up of the colony showing autozooid with proximal tubercles. D. Enlargement of the colony showing ancestrula and interzooecial avicularia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6580806" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6580806/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="33">Fig. 11B</figureCitation>
). Two conspicuous tubercles at distolateral corners of each autozooid (
<figureCitation id="130C2CF3DE4FFFF1FF46F174FEA14F18" box="[196,307,811,837]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="17.[189,232,1894,1920]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,1037,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-192@17.[189,1398,1037,1853]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Fig. 11. Labioporella hariparensis Guha &amp; Gopikrishna, 2007 (GIS/B 0533). A. General view of the colony showing autozooids. B. Enlargement of an autozooid showing cryptocyst and polypide tube. C. Close-up of the colony showing autozooid with proximal tubercles. D. Enlargement of the colony showing ancestrula and interzooecial avicularia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6580806" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6580806/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="33">Fig. 11C</figureCitation>
). Opesia rounded quadrangular, wider than long with smooth curved distally. Avicularia small, interzooecial, oval; cryptocyst narrow; opesia large, oval with broader proximal; rostrum thick, prominent, next distal zooid arise from rostral margin of avicularia (
<figureCitation id="130C2CF3DE4FFFF1FC5FF12EFBDB4FD1" box="[989,1097,881,908]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="17.[189,232,1894,1920]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,1037,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-192@17.[189,1398,1037,1853]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Fig. 11. Labioporella hariparensis Guha &amp; Gopikrishna, 2007 (GIS/B 0533). A. General view of the colony showing autozooids. B. Enlargement of an autozooid showing cryptocyst and polypide tube. C. Close-up of the colony showing autozooid with proximal tubercles. D. Enlargement of the colony showing ancestrula and interzooecial avicularia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6580806" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6580806/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="33">Fig. 11D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="DF4860FEDE4EFFF0FF3FF5D7FE714BB4" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6580804" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6580804" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6580804/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="32" startId="16.[189,232,1928,1954]" targetBox="[189,1398,809,1889]" targetPageId="16">
