<subSubSection id="C32D63FDDE4CFFF2FF3FF356FBBA4E5C" pageId="18" pageNumber="34" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B883076DE4CFFF2FF3FF356FEA24D7E" blockId="18.[189,304,265,291]" box="[189,304,265,291]" pageId="18" pageNumber="34">
<heading id="D0C0871ADE4CFFF2FF3FF356FEA24D7E" bold="true" box="[189,304,265,291]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="18" pageNumber="34" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B943EC64DE4CFFF2FF3FF356FEA24D7E" bold="true" box="[189,304,265,291]" pageId="18" pageNumber="34">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B883076DE4CFFF2FF3FF368FBBA4E5C" blockId="18.[187,1399,311,514]" pageId="18" pageNumber="34">
The present species shows a superficial resemblance to 
<taxonomicName id="4C374BF5DE4CFFF2FCCCF368FAE54D0F" authority="Canu &amp; Bassler, 1935" authorityName="Canu &amp; Bassler" authorityYear="1935" box="[846,1399,311,338]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Steginoporellidae" genus="Labioporella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="18" pageNumber="34" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="filiparietis">
<emphasis id="B943EC64DE4CFFF2FCCCF368FBF84D0C" box="[846,1130,311,337]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="34">Labioporella filiparietis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFA64D87DE4CFFF2FBF0F368FAE54D0F" author="Canu F. &amp; Bassler R. S." box="[1138,1399,311,338]" pageId="18" pageNumber="34" pagination="1 - 54" refId="ref7080" refString="Canu F. &amp; Bassler R. S. 1935. New species of Tertiary cheilostome Bryozoa from Victoria, Australia. Smithsonian miscellaneous collections 93: 1 - 54." type="journal article" year="1935">
Canu &amp; Bassler, 
<quantity id="4CCF9D93DE4CFFF2FABEF368FAE54D0F" box="[1340,1399,311,338]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.914899999999999" pageId="18" pageNumber="34" unit="in" value="1935.0">1935</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in the shape of the autozooids and the polypide tube but differs in having a granular cryptocyst, and the presence of avicularia and tubercles. The Aquitanian species 
<taxonomicName id="4C374BF5DE4CFFF2FCFFF322FF654DE6" authority="Guha &amp; Gopikrishna 2007" authorityName="Guha &amp; Gopikrishna" authorityYear="2007" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Steginoporellidae" genus="Labioporella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="18" pageNumber="34" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="bassleri">
<emphasis id="B943EC64DE4CFFF2FCFFF322FBE94DCA" box="[893,1147,381,407]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="34">Labioporella bassleri</emphasis>
Guha &amp; Gopikrishna 2007
</taxonomicName>
from Kharinadi Formation differs in not having avicularia or tubercles. The Gran Canarian Pliocene 
<taxonomicName id="4C374BF5DE4CFFF2FF39F39BFEED4D83" box="[187,383,452,478]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Steginoporellidae" genus="Labioporella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="18" pageNumber="34" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B943EC64DE4CFFF2FF39F39BFEC74D83" box="[187,341,452,478]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="34">Labioporella</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
<bibRefCitation id="EFA64D87DE4CFFF2FE04F39BFD0D4D83" author="Sendino C. &amp; Taylor P. D." box="[390,671,452,478]" pageId="18" pageNumber="34" pagination="229 - 239" refId="ref8207" refString="Sendino C. &amp; Taylor P. D. 2014. Pliocene bryozoans from Gran Canaria. In: Rosso A., Wyse Jackson P. N. &amp; Porter J. S. (eds) Bryozoan Studies 2013: 229 - 239. Museo delle Scienze, Trento. http: // www 2. muse. it / pubblicazioni / riviste. asp? tipo = 18" type="journal article" year="2014">Sendino &amp; Taylor, 2014</bibRefCitation>
differs from the present species in the absence of avicularia, a stout polypide tube and the distal margin of the opesia is higher than wide.
</paragraph>
